| DS-P1-002 | High | Partner booking fulfillment | Remove raw partner re-binding from booking mutation endpoints and use the authenticated partner principal consistently. Several `IsAdminOrPartnerSessionToken` routes still call `PartnerProfile.objects.filter(partner_session_token=...)` inside the handler, which allows cross-tenant booking/document/complaint actions whenever a foreign token is supplied. | open | `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:394-643`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:646-940`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:1378-1774` |
| DS-P1-003 | High | Booking documents and payouts | Make `DocumentsStatus` and `PartnersBookingPayment` one-row-per-booking structures and recalculate completion flags on document delete. The current FK + `get_or_create` pattern, first-row workflow read, and delete path can leave duplicated state rows, stale document completion flags, and duplicate partner receivable records. | open | `booking/models.py:172-181`; `booking/models.py:266-279`; `booking/workflow.py:215-225`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:556-640`; `booking/services.py:734-766` |
