| DS-P1-001 | Critical | Partner auth/profile/account | Replace legacy `AllowAny` self-service routes with authenticated partner permissions and stop trusting raw `partner_session_token` values for profile, OTP, address, bank, withdrawal, logo, and password operations. The same serializer currently returns `partner_session_token`, `firebase_token`, and `web_firebase_token`, so leaked profile payloads become reusable bearer credentials. | open | `partners/partner_profile.py:334-1295`; `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py:15-344`; `partners/serializers.py:214-229` |
| DS-P1-002 | High | Partner booking fulfillment | Remove raw partner re-binding from booking mutation endpoints and use the authenticated partner principal consistently. Several `IsAdminOrPartnerSessionToken` routes still call `PartnerProfile.objects.filter(partner_session_token=...)` inside the handler, which allows cross-tenant booking/document/complaint actions whenever a foreign token is supplied. | open | `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:394-643`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:646-940`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:1378-1774` |
| DS-P1-003 | High | Booking documents and payouts | Make `DocumentsStatus` and `PartnersBookingPayment` one-row-per-booking structures and recalculate completion flags on document delete. The current FK + `get_or_create` pattern, first-row workflow read, and delete path can leave duplicated state rows, stale document completion flags, and duplicate partner receivable records. | open | `booking/models.py:172-181`; `booking/models.py:266-279`; `booking/workflow.py:215-225`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:556-640`; `booking/services.py:734-766` |
| DS-P1-004 | High | Wallet withdrawals | Add row locking for wallet debits in both customer and partner withdrawal flows. Balance validation currently happens before the atomic write and without `select_for_update`, so concurrent requests can oversubscribe or overwrite wallet balances. | open | `common/api_v1.py:218-256`; `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py:235-264` |
| DS-P1-005 | Medium | Dead routes and duplicate package logic | Remove or reroute dead admin views and prune duplicated legacy operator package classes so the live route surface matches the maintained code. `GetAllApprovedCompaniesView` and `ManageFeaturedPackageView` are defined but unmounted; routed operator package endpoints already use `partners/package_management_operator.py`. | open | `management/urls.py:6-15`; `management/approval_task.py:907-990`; `management/approval_task.py:1282-1333`; `partners/urls.py:32-48`; `partners/package_management.py` |
| DS-P1-006 | Medium | Management QA coverage | Restore dedicated management tests for company approval, payment review, receivable transfer, and master-hotel catalog flows. This module currently has no live test file, and Phase 1 runtime verification stopped before discovery because Django is not installed in the current shell. | open | `rg --files /Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Backend/management`; `python3 manage.py test partners.tests booking.tests common.tests --settings=huz.settings_test` |
| SEC-001 | Critical | `common/authentication.py`, `partners/partner_profile.py`, `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py`, `booking/manage_partner_booking.py` | Legacy session-token transport is still accepted across customer and partner flows, including high-value mutation routes, so bearer-equivalent secrets can still travel in query strings and request bodies. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
| SEC-002 | Critical | `common/firebase.json`, `huz/settings.py` | Firebase service-account credentials are tracked in the repository and loaded by default from `common/firebase.json`; rotate the credential and move it to an env-controlled or external secret path. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
| SEC-003 | High | `partners/partner_profile.py`, `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py` | Legacy partner profile and wallet routes remain `AllowAny` while resolving principals directly from `partner_session_token`, making profile, banking, and withdrawal surfaces depend on raw token possession rather than explicit authenticated principals. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
| SEC-004 | Medium | `huz/settings.py`, `huz/urls.py`, `common/utility.py`, `booking/models.py`, `partners/models.py` | Uploaded passport, payment, complaint, and partner-company documents are stored in local media and can become anonymously reachable if `SERVE_MEDIA_AND_STATIC_FROM_DJANGO` is enabled; confirm production flag discipline and media exposure controls. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
| SEC-005 | Critical | `partners/package_management.py`, `partners/serializers.py` | Anonymous website package endpoints serialize `partner_session_token` in normal package list/detail payloads, allowing public users to harvest operator auth tokens directly from catalog traffic. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 1 |
| SEC-006 | Critical | `booking/serializers.py`, `booking/views/bookings.py`, `booking/manage_partner_booking.py` | Booking APIs disclose the opposite party's session token in customer and partner responses, creating a direct cross-role impersonation path between customers and operators. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 1 |
| SEC-007 | Critical | `common/user_profile.py`, `common/serializers.py`, `partners/partner_profile.py`, `partners/serializers.py` | Public existence/profile endpoints return full serialized user and partner records, including session tokens and Firebase device tokens, instead of safe yes/no lookup results. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 1 |
| SEC-008 | Critical | `common/user_profile.py`, `common/utility.py`, `common/authentication.py` | Customer `session_token` values are deterministically derived from phone numbers with base64 encoding and are accepted by the auth bridge, so any known phone number can be turned into a bearer-equivalent token offline. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 1 |
